      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MINOS NZ (11) did a great job from a similar draw in round one last week, taking off around the field midrace to find the front before digging deep to go under narrowly at this circuit and distance. Charged home to get within 2.5m off Leap To Fame prior so he is in form and well up to winning this with even luck. SPEAK THE TRUTH (4) was runner-up in the final of this series last year and looks to be working his way back into that sort of form, coming from wider to place last week. Owns a strong strike rate at this circuit and distance and will be close to his peak fourth up. CAPTAINS KNOCK (3) only beat one home when resuming last week but he had little go his way from a back row draw. Much better barrier here so look for big improvement. CHEERSTOLOU (7) draws wide so may need a little luck but was held up late when only 4.4m away last week. Must include.",
